  "market_context": "After a daily expansion followed by retracement, ETH formed a swing high on the daily chart. The analyst dropped to hourly to confirm bearish bias via change in state of delivery and identified a bearish breaker block after sweeping a prior high.",
  "key_observation": "A sweep of a prior high created a bearish breaker block (high-low-higher-high-lower-low sequence) on hourly and 5-minute, enabling a high-probability continuation short with 2R target.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily chart, the analyst observed an expansion, retracement, and then formation of a swing high, indicating potential bearish continuation or retracement.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to the hourly chart to confirm bearish bias by identifying a change in state of delivery (closure through opposing down-close candles).",
    "Step 3: Identified a bearish breaker block on the hourly after price swept a prior high, forming a high-low-higher-high-lower-low sequence; marked the down-close candles as the breaker zone.",
    "Step 4: Dropped to the 5-minute chart to refine entry, confirming the same breaker structure after sweeping highs and forming a lower low, then marked the retest of the down-close candle as the entry zone.",
    "Step 5: Placed stop above the breaker block high and targeted 2R, which was achieved as price continued lower."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit 2R target successfully.",
  "lessons": "Wait for structural confirmation (swing high + change in state of delivery) before entering; use breaker blocks on aligned time frames for high-probability continuation entries with tight risk and 2R reward.",
